HEADWORD: Averruncator
<hw>Av`er*run*ca"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An instrument
for pruning trees, having two blades, or a blade and a hook, fixed on a
long rod and operated by a string or wire; a tree pruner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

